,"ref":"23d78ff2-f2ea-43e4-986f-c93daa1e3a4d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 6","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"data":{"reference":"f6ca0070-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"68b3f439-d2dc-442d-b7de-7d5260ad053b","nodes":[{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"eed7617f-c048-49b2-8aff-084fbe84532a","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Bonds","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"f6ca0070-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"230b2f2d-2804-480c-b326-e408cfe4d8cd","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"458718b5-638e-4ac9-817a-f55623d8d80d","nodes":[{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"f8233931-c312-469c-ba63-ccad22068b8b","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 7","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]}],"data":{"reference":"fe68fd90-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}}],"data":{}},{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"59bbe062-825c-4247-a85c-bf474478fd29","nodes":[{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"34b0d00e-1699-41ed-9e29-b5c7f2adcc89","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Stock Valuation","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"fe68fd90-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}}],"data":{}}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":"ul_none"},"ref":"4ac214bd-2135-4c9c-8ee5-124b938489e3"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group  Sidebar_1Aside","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"d5fd5876-c617-4ebd-ae52-5fc1f6ebcc34","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Valuation Principle Connection.","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"object":"text","text":" In this part of the text, we introduce the basic tools for making financial decisions. ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"93e51937-27ea-4edc-af27-c1efce0d7342","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 3","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"eca039c0-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" presents the most important idea in this book, the ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"Valuation Principle","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":". The Valuation Principle states that we can use market prices to determine the value of an investment opportunity to the firm. As we progress through our study of corporate finance, we will demonstrate that the Valuation Principle is the one unifying principle that underlies all of finance and links all the ideas throughout this book.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"f869af58-e7ef-47c6-ac1c-589ae864c3d7"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"e693836c-b1e0-415a-af7f-6b58ab30aa2a","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Every day, managers in companies all over the world make financial decisions. These range from relatively minor decisions such as a local hardware store owner’s determination of when to restock inventory, to major decisions such as Apple’s 2010 launch of the iPad, Microsoft’s 2015 software overhaul launching Windows 10, and Disney’s 2019 decision to launch its own video streaming service. What do these diverse decisions have in common? They all were made by comparing the costs of the action against the value to the firm of the benefits. Specifically, a company’s managers must determine what it is worth to the company today to receive the project’s future cash inflows while paying its cash outflows.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"e27aed47-129e-4910-94fc-fadd518ca36c"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"9a2c9b63-d482-4130-aac7-a8a25dd4a2ee","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"In ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"7e7d5f11-2ca2-4b23-bdae-bb44ebdb632d","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 3","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"eca039c0-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", we start to build the tools to undertake this analysis with a central concept in financial economics—the ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"time value of money.","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":" In ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"a951b61f-27be-48a4-ab9b-45fef9a1681f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 4","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"ef938920-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", we explain how to value any series of future cash flows and derive a few useful shortcuts for valuing various types of cash flow patterns. ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"b83e4853-3562-4728-8c53-dcdd48f18009","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 5","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"f2603db0-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" discusses how interest rates are quoted in the market and how to handle interest rates that compound more frequently than once per year. In ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"40383d67-1457-400c-a90d-547934c61d99","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 6","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"f6ca0070-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", we will apply what we have learned about interest rates and the present value of cash flows to the task of valuing bonds. In the last chapter of ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"1a359e82-6c7c-47ca-9346-074ef1e20b90","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Part 2","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"eb58ecb0-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"7a967907-fcbc-4b35-ae16-004c1340366e","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Chapter 7","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"fe68fd90-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":", we discuss the features of common stocks and learn how to calculate an estimate of their value.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"d3acf24d-1b0c-4cbf-b6ec-b07b98caa4fd"}]}]}]}]},"screenType":"","transitions":{"enter":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""},"exit":{"animation":"","duration":0,"easing":"","customKeyframes":""}},"lockElements":false,"learnerCurrentAttempt":1,"footer":{"buttonText":"Next","buttonIcon":"Arrow","showFooter":false,"showHistoryNavButtons":false,"previewFooter":false,"position":"Fixed to screen bottom","footerComponent":{"showFooterDropArea":"hide","width":100,"footerComponentsAlignment":"right"}},"styles":{"background":{},"stage":{"maxWidth":940,"background":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","responsive":true,"padding":{"vertical":60,"horizontal":60},"border":{"color":"rgba(224, 224, 224, 1)","radius":0,"width":0}},"elements":{"padding":{"vertical":10,"horizontal":10}},"footer":{"buttonColor":"rgba(0, 115, 202, 1)","textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","padding":10,"corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 -1px 4px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06), 0 0 12px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"},"feedback":{"width":320,"textColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7)","backgroundColor":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 1)","corners":4,"border":"none","shadow":"0 5px 47px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.15), 0 10px 20px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1), 0 7px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.1)"}},"title":"Part 2"},"assets":[],"scenarios":[],"pluginPayload":{"pluginRepositoryPath":"https://plugin-repository-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8/0.15.209/ac43ee4c0eda05e9718fa83a5aed4cff.zip","summary":{"pluginId":"9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8","name":"Screen","description":"A screen of a lesson","type":"screen","latestVersion":"0.15.209","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","createdAt":"Fri, 6 Mar 2020 04:11:39 GMT","updatedAt":"Tue, 13 Dec 2022 22:07:46 GMT"